Letter to Kim Jong Il from NDFSK CC 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a letter from the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea on July 27 on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the victory in the Korean War.
 The letter said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The July 27 victory in the Korean War which startled the world half a century ago was an event of the century that humbled the pride of the U.S. imperialists, who had boasted of being "the strongest" in the world for the first time in history and opened a new era of independence against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the historic July 27 victory, the north could top the world as heroic Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You are now brilliantly carrying forward the history of the victory in the war against the U.S. won by President Kim Il Sung, a peerlessly brilliant commander and a national hero, in the middle of the last century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the great result of your Songun policy, an all-powerful treasured sword, that the north is honorably defending the sovereignty of the nation and the fortress of socialism while foiling the unprecedented north-stifling offensive of the U.S.  fancying itself as the "only superpower" of the world, and leading the cause of global independence to victory, while striking a resolute blow at the high-handed strategy of the U.S. for world domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest honor and good fortune of the 70 million Koreans to hold in high esteem as the leader of the nation you, who are carrying forward the July 27 of the 20th century as that of the 21st century with your Songun policy best in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialists ultimately ignite a war of aggression against the north, the NDFSK and all the South Koreans, together with compatriots in the north, will wage a life-and-death battle to achieve the historic cause of national reunification at all costs.

DPRK War Victory anniversary celebrated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Moscow, July 25 (KCNA) -- The party for peace and unity of Russia sponsored a meeting in Moscow on July 23 to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the Korean people's victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War.
 Chairwoman of the party Sazhi Umalatova, addressing the meeting, said that the gifted military strategy and distinguished commanding art of President Kim Il Sung brought about the victory of the Korean people in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Georgy Trapeznikov, president of the International Academy of Mental Unity of the World People, said that leader Kim Jong Il's Songun policy made the national power of Korea invincible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that Kim Jong Il is now creditably carrying forward the cause of Kim Il Sung, prof. Olga Ishenko, doctor of history, noted that his Songun policy is a model to be followed by many countries.

Sister cities between DPRK and Mexico 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) -- A ceremony for setting Chiautempan city, Tlaxcala state, Mexico, and Nampho city, the DPRK, as sister cities was held in Chiautempan on July 19.
 The mayor of the city and the DPRK ambassador to Mexico signed a document on establishing sister cities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony the mayor said that the establishment of sister city with Nampho, a famous port city in Korea, is a clear example of the friendly and cooperative relations deepening between the two countries and the two peoples as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will organize colorful political and cultural functions for solidarity with the Korean people in our city and take these opportunities to contribute to the development of the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries, he stressed.

U.S. warned not to forget past defeat 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) -- the U.S. imperialists should not repeat the lesson of their disgraceful defeat in the Korean war, contemplating why they were defeated, warns Rodong Sinmun today.
 Commenting on the U.S. moves to unleash another war in Korea, intentionally rendering the situation strained, the paper says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Peaceful solution to the nuclear issue" on the lip-service of the U.S. is nothing but a camouflaged peace trick and a window-dressing to cover up its intention for a preemptive attack. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and the people of the DPRK do not want a war. But they are not afraid of and will not avoid it. It is utter folly for the U.S. to think that its troops will go scot-free when they are relocated in areas south of seoul. The U.S. should not think that its forces present in South Korea will survive another Korean war to be ignited by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years the U.S. had unilateral wars of aggression, in which it would beat the "enemy" by applying "surgical operation-style strike" in long distance, without being counterattacked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, such way of war can never work on the Korean army and people who have strong war deterrent force under the great Songun policy.

Papers on exploits of Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate editorials to the 50th anniversary of the victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War, which say that the exploits president  Kim Il Sung performed in achieving the victory in the war will shine forever under the Songun policy.
 Rodong Sinmun says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president led the Fatherland Liberlation War to the brilliant victory, which becomes immortal historic exploits he performed on behalf of the times and revolution, the Korean nation and the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of outstanding and seasoned leadership of Kim Jong Il holds a brilliant place in the glorious 50-year long history of the Korean revolution, which has emerged victorious on the basis of the immortal exploits the president performed in achieving victory in the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history, in which Kim Jong Il has led our army and people for scores of years, is the history in which he has provided all the guarantees for eternal victory in the confrontation with the imperialists with his Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has successfully carried forward and developed in depth the president's idea and line of attaching importance to arms and set forth the political mode of Songun, a powerful socialist political mode, and opened the era of new victory in the anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. confrontation with the might of Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exploits in achieving the victory in the war are most precious for us who should fight the imperialists to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should firmly hold fast to the exploits in achieving the victory in the war to resolutely defend our ideology, system and cause and glorify the era of the great Songun policy as the era of new victory in the confrontation with the imperialists and the era of the great prosperity and welfare of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that though half a century has passed and generations have been replaced since the very day of the victory in the war, the immortal exploits of the president and the feats of the Korean army and people in achieving victory in the war will shine long under Kim Jong Il's Songun leadership.

Congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il today received a congratulatory message from the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War.
 The victory in the Fatherland Liberlation War represented a victory of the idea of attaching importance to arms, the idea of attaching importance to military affairs set out by  President Kim Il Sung and a shining victory of his matchless grit, outstanding military strategy and tactics, the message says. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has built the country into an invincible country strong in politico-ideological and military terms. His Songun policy enjoys unquestioned support of the people and the world progressives praise the policy as a perfect political mode as it is a patriotic political mode that provides a sure guarantee for the security of the nation and the accomplishment of the cause of national reunification, the desire of the fellow countrymen, it says. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indeed, the dignity and sovereignty of the country and nation are firmly safeguarded and the country and the people will soon see a new era of history in which the country is reunified and prosperous as he stands in the van, it notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongryon will firmly believe Kim Jong Il and keep to the patriotic road despite the desperate efforts of the enemies and difficulties lying in the way ahead, the message adds.

Wreaths laid before Friendship Tower 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials, officers and men of the Korean People's Army and working people laid wreaths before the friendship tower this morning on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War.
 The KPA guards of honor were lined up at the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were han song ryong, sin il nam, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party Kim Yong Dae, officials of the party and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, kpa officers and men and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chinese ambassador to the DPRK wu donghe and embassy officials were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A wreath was laid in the joint name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the DPRK cabinet and a wreath in the name of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then wreaths were laid in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, ministries, national institutions, organs  of science, public heath and the press, party and power organs and factories in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of the wreaths were letters "Glory to the martyrs of the Chinese people's volunteers" the participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the martyrs of the Chinese people's volunteers who died while heroically fighting in the last Korean War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, wreaths were laid before the martyrs' cemeteries of the Chinese People's Volunteers across the country.

Wreaths laid before martyrs cemeteries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 27 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials, servicemen and working people in the DPRK laid wreaths before the revolutionary martyrs cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the patriotic martyrs cemetery this morning on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War.
 Seen on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries were wreaths from General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA guards of honor were standing in the cemeteries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participating in the wreath-laying ceremonies were Hong Song Nam, Kye Ung Thae and other senior officials, officials of party, armed forces and power bodies, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicemen and working people in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were placed before the cemeteries in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also wreaths were laid in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces and other ministries, national institutions, KPA units, scientific, educational, cultural and art, public health and press organs, and party and power organs, factories and farms in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of wreaths were letters "Glory to the revolutionary martyrs" and "glory to the patriotic martyrs" the participants observed a silent tribute to the memory of the revolutionary and patriotic martyrs who devoted their all to achieving the liberation of the country, freedom and happiness of the people and the reunification of the country and accomplishing the revolutionary cause of juche under the wise guidance of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the military attaches corps here laid a wreath before the cemetery on Mt. Taesong.

Military ranks of KPA commanding officers promoted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il issued an order on promoting the military ranks of commanding officers of the KPA on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War.
 The order dated July 26 said that the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK fully demonstrated the mettle and honor of heroic Korea by defeating the U.S. imperialist aggressors, which had boasted of being "the strongest" in the world, under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today they have grown stronger to be a matchless army capable of crushing any imperialist aggressors at a single stroke and are performing proud feats to shine long in the annals of the country, standing in the van of the struggle to defend the country and build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He issued this order, expressing the firm belief that the kpa commanding officers who have grown under the care of the Workers' Party of Korea and the leader would creditably fulfil in the future, too, the heavy duties they have assumed before the party, the country, the times and the revolution, true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the order, Pyon In Son and five other commanding officers have been promoted to colonel generals, Jon Ryong Gu and nine others to lieutenant generals and Rim Yong Hwa and seven others to major generals.

War Victory Day observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held in the compound of the monument to victory in the Fatherland Liberlation War today to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the victory in the great war.
 Present at the meeting were senior party, state and army officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on hand were the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea and overseas compatriots staying in the socialist homeland. Present on invitation were diplomatic envoys of different countries to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Chun, chief of the general staff of the Korean People's Army, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that the Fatherland Liberlation War waged by the Korean people was a worldwide revolutionary war against the armed invasion of the allied imperialist forces led by the U.S. and a liberation war of justice to defend the sovereignty and dignity of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic victory of our army and people in the war was a brilliant victory of President Kim Il Sung's Juche-based military idea, strategy and tactics and unique war methods, he stated, referring to the enduring feats the president performed in leading the anti-U.S. war to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Fatherland Liberlation War of the Korean people convincingly proved that the army and people intensely loyal to their great leader's guidance could finally win in the confrontation with any formidable imperialist enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people always remember the progressive humankind of the world who rendered full support to them in the fight of justice during the war, and the Chinese people who dispatched volunteers formed with their fine sons and daughters to the Korean front and helped the Korean people at the cost of their blood, and are grateful for this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This war teaches the immovable truth that the singlehearted unity of the party, army and people around their great leader is the best treasured sword of victory capable of defeating any formidable enemy armed with sophisticated weapons. It also instills into the Korean people the strong revolutionary faith that with this sword, the DPRK will surely emerge victorious in the present confrontation with the U.S. though it is rigorous and hard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Korean revolution is making a vigorous advance on a higher stage, recording a new chapter of victory in the history of the struggle against the U.S.-led imperialists with the ever-victorious revolutionary armed forces under the distinguished Songun leadership of supreme commander Kim Jong Il who is creditably carrying forward the President's cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun revolutionary line and the Songun policy are the strategic line and political mode that should always be held fast to as long as imperialism remains on the earth and the enemy resorts to aggressive moves, the reporter said, urging all the party members, KPA officers and men and people to remain true to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed the need to continue directing enormous efforts to the increase of military capability so as to firmly prepare the people's army politically, ideologically and in military technique and cement the singlehearted unity of the army and the people as firm as a rock. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for carrying through the line of economic construction in the Songun era on preferentially developing the defence industry to provide a sure guarantee for the nation's defence capability and maintaining production upswing in all fields of socialist construction and thus glorifying the 55th anniversary of the DPRK with proud achievements in work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the arrogant and outrageous moves of the U.S. imperialists to stifle the DPRK by force are being carried into extremes, he declared that the army and the people of the DPRK will promptly beat back any "precision strike", "surgical operation-style strike" and "preemptive nuclear attack" with the powerful war deterrent force which they have built up through all hardships, tightening their belts under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. belligerent group and its followers dare unleash a war in defiance of our warnings, they will not be able to avoid the merciless crushing blow of the army of the DPRK and they will suffer a miserable defeat dwarfing that they met in the past Korean war, he warned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He concluded that all the Koreans in the north, the south and abroad will more vigorously wage the anti-war, anti-U.S. struggle through national cooperation under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and thus surely achieve the historic desire of national reunification and build an independent, reunified great prosperous powerful nation in this land without fail.

Inter-Korean contact made
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) -- A contact between the Korea Asia-Pacific Peace Committee and Hyundai Asan was made at the Mt. Kumgang resort from Wednesday to Friday.
 Attending the contact from the north side were Ri Jong Hyok, vice-chairman of the Korea Asia-Pacific Peace Committee, Pang Jong Sam, president of the Kumgangsan International Tourist General Company, and other officials concerned and on the Hyundai Asan side were chairman of Hyundai Asan Jong Mong Hon, its president Kim Yun Gyu and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They had an exhaustive discussion on immediate and important issues including the definition of the boundary of Mt. Kumgang tourist zone, trial overland tour and other issues instrumental in revitalizing Mt. Kumgang tour and the issue of holding the ceremony of opening the Ryugyong Jong Ju Yong Gymnasium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides agreed to examine the issues from a positive stand.

Anniversary of Cuban Revolution observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) -- The Korean people extend warm congratulations and militant salute to the fraternal Cuban people on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the July 26 Armed Uprising, say papers here today.
 Rodong Sinmun in a signed article says that the first gunfire of revolution made at Moncada on July 26 by Cuban revolutionaries under the leadership of Fidel Castro, the Supreme Leader of the Cuban revolution, is brilliantly recorded in the history of the Cuban people's revolutionary struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the arduous revolutionary struggle the Cuban people learned the precious truth that the security and peace of the country and the victory of socialism can be guaranteed only by arms of justice, the article notes, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cuban people, closely rallied around their leader, have successfully pushed forward the revolution and construction, maintaining their faith in socialism despite the U.S. imperialists' persistent anti-Cuba moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The national power of Cuba is growing stronger and its external relations are expanding as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people highly appreciate the achievements made by the Cuban people and extend full support and solidarity to their just cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary ties between the peoples of the DPRK and Cuba are being boosted and the bilateral friendship is growing stronger with each passing day in the course of the hard struggle against the common enemies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson in a signed article says that the gunfire made at Moncada on July 26, 1953 helped the Cuban people enshrine the precious truth that an armed enemy can be defeated only with arms and freedom, liberation and the victory of the revolution can be guaranteed only by arms of revolution.

50th anniversary of War Victory celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) -- The 50th anniversary of the victory in the Great Fatherland Liberlation War was celebrated in Korea.
 An art performance "Song of victory will be everlasting under the leadership of the Great General" was given by members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union on July 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance reflected the immortal exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung in leading the war to victory and the ardent patriotism, fighting spirit and revolutionary optimism displayed by people and women in the rear who actively assisted servicemen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A national art contest was held on the same day among fine art circle members at School Children's Palaces (houses) across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented to the contest were fine art works including Korean paintings, posters, pencil drawings, comics and calligraphic works representing the mindset of schoolchildren who are stately growing up as masters of future for a great prosperous powerful nation.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il received gifts from the participants in the International Conference for Peace on the Korean Peninsula and Solidarity Functions held on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the Korean people's victory in the Fatherland Liberlation War.
 They included executive secretary of the world peace council athanasios pafilis: president of the Women's International Democratic Federation Marcia De Campos Pereira: honorary chairman of the Asian Regional Committee to Support Korea's Reunification and chairman of the Sri Lanka-people's Korea Friendship Association Reggie Ranatunge: first vice-chairman of the Latin American and Caribbean Regional Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification and chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru Genaro Ledesma Izquieta: member of the National Council of the central committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxist-Leninist) and president of the Council for People's Welfare of the Nepalese Royal Government Naresh Man Shakya: chairman of the c.c., the Workers' Party of Bangladesh and chairman of the Bangladesh Committee for Solidarity with the Korean people Rashed Khan Menon who is vice-chairman of the Asian Regional Committee to Support Korea's Reunification: Representative of the Arab RegionalGgroup for Probing the Truth behind GIS' Atrocities Marwan Sudah, chairman of the Arab Committee for Solidarity with the Korean People and Supporting the Reunification of Korea: chairman of the Ffrican Regional Committee for Friendship and Solidarity with the Korean People and chairman of the Benin-Korea Amicable Association "long live Kim Jong Il, Supreme Leader" Hessou Kohovi: chairman of the Germany-DPRK Association Hans Haubenschild: member of the East European Regional Group for Probing the Truth behind GIS' Atrocities Aleksandr Brezhnev: and the delegation of the Mongolia-Korea Friendship Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, he was also presented with gifts by the Council for People's Welfare of the Nepalese Royal Government, the Spain Association for the Friendship with Korea, the Nepalese Afro-Asian People's Solidarity Committee and the Germany-DPRK Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gifts were handed to officials concerned.

DPRK history society on significance of War Victory
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 26 (KCNA) -- The Korean people's victory in the Fatherland Liberlation War was a great event that brought about a turn in the implementation of the cause of independence against imperialism, exploding the myth about the U.S. imperialists' "mightiness".
 The DPRK history society stresses this in a memorandum contributed to Rodong Sinmun today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean War was, in political aspect, a model of anti-imperialist national liberation struggles, a war in which socialism defeated imperialism for the first time after the Second World War and, in moral aspect, a fight between human being and "higher savage," a war that declared the ruin of the "Yankee civilization". In military and technical aspects, it was the war largest ever in history in scale except the past two world wars and the first war in the era of a-bombs, a war in which most advanced weaponry was used at that time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The myth about the U.S. imperialists' "mightiness" meant, in essence, the "mightiness" of the U.S. military capability, that is its tremendous economic potential and the superiority of its aggression troops in numerical strength and military technique based on such potential, the memorandum says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, that myth was shattered to smithereens in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the three year-long Korean War, the U.S. imperialists hurled over two million troops and all types of modern military equipment and weapons. But, even their "ever-victorious division", B-29 called "superfortress", seventh fleet with missouri as its flag ship and hundreds of warships of the navy in the far east could not save the U.S. from its defeat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the Second World War the U.S. suffered a loss of 46,000 planes in the wide skies of the world in four years. However, in the Korean War it lost more than 12,000 planes in the small skies over the Korean Peninsula, one thousandths of that size, only in three years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists were so foolish as to calculate that if they erased the cities and rural villages of Korea from a "map", set fire to mountains and streams, plants and trees and killed at random men and women, old and young through a "mass killing operation" involving the use of even germ and chemical weapons, they could frighten the Korean people and demonstrate the U.S. "mightiness". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But they could not bring the Korean people to their knees by any barbarous atrocities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That was why former U.S. defense secretary marshall deplored that the myth was shattered, saying the U.S. was not so strong as others thought. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., the "superpower" that suffered not a single defeat in the 100 odd year-long history of war of aggression, sustained a disgraceful defeat for the first time before the young people's army in Korea and the myth about the "mightiness" of the U.S. imperialists was shattered to smithereens. The memorandum refers to the worldwide significance of the victory in the Fatherland Liberlation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The victory in the war helped protect the security of the socialist countries and the world peace and further strengthen the socialist forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The victory brought about a new surge in the anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. struggle and the national liberation struggle, precipitated the collapse of the imperialist colonial system as a whole and thus occasioned an epochal turn in the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the military and technological superiority in which the U.S. imperialists had believed as in "God" proved absurd and the corruption of the U.S. imperialist aggression troops was brought to light in the Korean War, hundreds of millions of oppressed people, of the world who were taken in by the idea of fearing and worshiping the U.S., were freed from the mental yoke and joined the anti-imperialist front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world people came to view the U.S. as a "clay-moulded giant" and a "paper tiger", not an "invincible power". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They grasped the truth that a decisive factor of winning a victory in the revolutionary war lies in the united strength of the popular masses convinced of the validity of their cause, not in the advantages of the combat equipment and, accordingly, even a small country can surely defeat any formidable enemy and win a final victory if it fights against him in a do-or-die spirit, singleheartedly rallied around its leader, believing in its strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The example of the anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. struggle set by the Korean people in the Fatherland Liberlation War served as a banner of the national liberation struggle in colonies and a factor of opening an epochal turn in the struggle for global independence.
